Griner and Johnson have not said when or where they plan to get married.

The widespread reporting of the engagement and its positive reception was unthinkable just a few years ago, when despite a large proportion of lesbian fans and many gay players, the WNBA shied away from acknowledging it.

Earlier this year, the WNBA announced that it would actively begin marketing the sport to its lesbian fans, and teams and individual players have participated in gay pride events.

